verbose_text: In a recent double-blind, randomised, placebo controlled trial involving 737 adults who were at least 65 years of age (mean 74.4 years) and who had persisting subclinical hypothyroidism (TSH level 4.60 to 19.99 mIU/l; free thyroxine level within the reference range), no apparent benefits in alleviation of symptoms were obtained during one-year observation [XREF_BIBR].
